1f.gif","alt":"The figure shows the annual drug overdose death rates for selected prescription and illicit drugs in Florida for 2003-2009. Among seven specific drugs examined, in 2003 the highest death rate was for cocaine (3.2 per 100,000 population), followed by methadone (2.2), oxycodone (1.7), heroin (1.4), morphine and alprazolam (1.3), and hydrocodone (1.1). In 2009, the number of deaths involving prescription drugs was four times the number involving illicit drugs, and the highest death rate was for oxycodone (6.4 per 100,00 population), followed by alprazolam (4.4), methadone (3.9), cocaine (2.8), morphine (1.6), hydrocodone (1.4), and heroin (0.5).","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":505,"renderedHeight":447,"naturalWidth":505,"naturalHeight":447,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 650 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":18050},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_out.png","alt":"External Web Site Icon","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":10,"renderedHeight":10,"naturalWidth":10,"naturalHeight":10,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":232},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16